## 3. Topologia Kafka — Topic e Consumer Groups

### Topic

| Topic | Produttori | Consumatori | Tipo messaggio | Chiave partizione |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `saga-events` | order, delivery, drone | order, drone | `SagaEvent` (JSON) | `order_id` |
| `order-requests` | order | delivery | `OrderMessage` (JSON) | `order_id` |
| `drone-requests` | delivery | drone | `OrderMessage` (JSON) | `order_id` |

### Consumer Groups

| Group ID | Servizio | Topic sottoscritto | Ruolo |
|---|---|---|---|
| `order-service` | order | `saga-events` | Avanza la SAGA su ogni step event |
| `delivery-service` | delivery | `order-requests` | Schedula delivery, inoltra a drone |
| `drone-service-orders` | drone | `drone-requests` | Assegna drone, avvia timer consegna |
| `drone-service-compensation` | drone | `saga-events` | Gestisce eventi `COMPENSATE_DRONE` |

.mermaid
    graph LR
        subgraph Topics["Topic Kafka"]
            SE["saga-events"]
            OR["order-requests"]
            DR["drone-requests"]
        end

        subgraph Groups["Consumer Groups"]
            G1["order-service"]
            G2["delivery-service"]
            G3["drone-service-orders"]
            G4["drone-service-compensation"]
        end

        SE -->|"subscribe"| G1
        SE -->|"subscribe"| G4
        OR -->|"subscribe"| G2
        DR -->|"subscribe"| G3

> **Consumer group semantics:** tutte le repliche dello stesso servizio condividono un `group.id`.
> Kafka distribuisce le partizioni tra di loro automaticamente (load balancing).
> Servizi con `group.id` diverso ricevono ciascuno una copia indipendente dello stream (fan-out).

## 4. Flusso completo — Happy Path

.mermaid
    sequenceDiagram
        actor Client
        participant O as Order Service
        participant MDB_O as MongoDB (order)
        participant K as Kafka
        participant D as Delivery Service
        participant DR as Drone Service
        participant MDB_D as MongoDB (drone)

        Client->>O: POST / {ordine}
        O->>O: genera order_id + saga_id
        O->>MDB_O: save SagaState (STARTED)
        O->>O: valida ordine (Step 1)
        O->>MDB_O: save SagaState (IN_PROGRESS, step: DeliveryScheduling)
        O->>K: produce → order-requests (OrderMessage, key=order_id)
        O-->>Client: 201 {order_id, saga_id}

        K->>D: consume order-requests (group: delivery-service)
        D->>D: genera delivery_id
        D->>K: produce → drone-requests (OrderMessage, key=order_id)
        D->>K: produce → saga-events (DeliveryScheduled, key=order_id)

        K->>O: consume saga-events (group: order-service)
        O->>O: match DeliveryScheduled
        O->>MDB_O: save SagaState (step: DroneAssignment)
        O->>K: commit offset

        K->>DR: consume drone-requests (group: drone-service-orders)
        DR->>MDB_D: save DroneEvent::Created (v0)
        DR->>K: produce → saga-events (DroneAssigned, key=order_id)
        DR->>MDB_D: save DroneEvent::Dispatched (v1)
        DR->>DR: aggiunge a in_flight map
        DR->>K: commit offset

        K->>O: consume saga-events (group: order-service)
        O->>O: match DroneAssigned
        O->>MDB_O: save SagaState (COMPLETED)
        O->>K: produce → saga-events (OrderCompleted, key=order_id)
        O->>K: commit offset

        Note over DR: scheduler ogni 10s
        DR->>DR: settle_arrived()
        DR->>MDB_D: save DroneEvent::Delivered (v2)
        DR->>MDB_D: save DroneEvent::Returned (v3)
        DR->>DR: rimuove da in_flight map

---

## 5. Flusso completo — Compensazione (fallimento Step 3)

.mermaid
    sequenceDiagram
        participant O as Order Service
        participant MDB_O as MongoDB (order)
        participant K as Kafka
        participant DR as Drone Service

        Note over K,O: DroneAssignmentFailed ricevuto (group: order-service)
        K->>O: consume saga-events
        O->>O: match DroneAssignmentFailed
        O->>MDB_O: save SagaState (FAILED)
        O->>MDB_O: save SagaState (COMPENSATING)
        O->>K: commit offset

        Note over O: steps_to_compensate() = [DroneAssignment, DeliveryScheduling, OrderValidation]

        O->>K: produce → saga-events (CompensateDrone, key=order_id)
        O->>K: produce → saga-events (CompensateDelivery, key=order_id)
        O->>K: produce → saga-events (CompensateOrder, key=order_id)

        K->>DR: consume saga-events (group: drone-service-compensation)
        DR->>DR: match CompensateDrone
        DR->>DR: compensate(drone_id) — rimuove da in_flight
        DR->>K: commit offset

        Note over DR,K: altri eventi (CompensateDelivery, CompensateOrder)\nricevuti dallo stesso consumer → match _ → commit immediato (skip)

        O->>MDB_O: save SagaState (COMPENSATED)
        O->>K: produce → saga-events (OrderCancelled, key=order_id)

---

## 6. Infrastruttura — Note sui listener Kafka

Kafka gira in **KRaft mode** (nessun Zookeeper). Il broker espone due listener:

| Listener | Indirizzo | Usato da |
|---|---|---|
| `PLAINTEXT` | `kafka:9092` | Container Docker (comunicazione inter-servizio) |
| `EXTERNAL` | `localhost:9094` | Macchina host (CLI Kafka, IDE, Kafka UI) |

La variabile d'ambiente per i servizi è `KAFKA_BROKERS=kafka:9092`.
Per accedere dall'host usare `localhost:9094`.
